I Am That is a modern classical book on Advaita (Nondualism) philosophy. It is a compilation of talks given by Sri Nisargadatta Maharaj, one of the great spiritual masters of the 20th century, who lived in Mumbai, India.The English translation of the book from the original Marathi was done by Maurice Frydman, edited by Sri Sudhakar S. Dixit and first published in 1973 by Chetana Publications. The book was revised and reedited in July 1981.Considered by many to be the author's masterpiece, I Am That has been translated into several languages since its first appearance.